WEBVTT

00:07.632 --> 00:11.302
(pensive instrumental music)

00:27.527 --> 00:30.280
(brooding music)

00:36.327 --> 00:39.330
(suspenseful music)

01:00.268 --> 01:02.187
- You okay, Mrs. Crane?

01:03.438 --> 01:05.607
- Yes.
- Can I get you anything?

01:05.607 --> 01:06.900
- No.

01:06.900 --> 01:09.903
(suspenseful music)

01:23.500 --> 01:27.295
(tire spokes clicking)

01:27.295 --> 01:32.300
(zombie snarling)
(suspenseful music)

01:46.106 --> 01:47.357
- Would you like to take a break?

01:47.357 --> 01:49.234
Maybe relax a bit?

01:49.234 --> 01:51.611
Sometimes, I lock myself in the bathroom

01:51.611 --> 01:53.321
and I take a nice long, hot shower.

01:53.321 --> 01:54.739
That usually does it for me.

01:56.491 --> 01:57.617
Did you need a few more minutes?

01:57.617 --> 01:58.451
- [Marion] Yes.

02:00.203 --> 02:02.622
- Would you like to go back upstairs?

02:02.622 --> 02:03.414
- No.

02:04.749 --> 02:05.625
Yes.

02:06.751 --> 02:08.795
He was a good man.

02:08.795 --> 02:10.463
You need to understand this?

02:12.340 --> 02:13.341
- It's okay, Marion.

02:14.342 --> 02:16.845
- Don't patronize me!

02:16.845 --> 02:18.638
He was a good man.

02:19.889 --> 02:21.891
It was his business that had the issue.

02:23.434 --> 02:26.104
(pensive music)

02:32.152 --> 02:34.112
(door creaking)

02:34.112 --> 02:36.781
(pensive music)

02:39.075 --> 02:40.410
(door creaking)

02:40.410 --> 02:43.079
(pensive music)

02:45.665 --> 02:47.250
- [Man] I am sorry.

02:49.794 --> 02:52.422
- Is there something else
you want to confess, my son?

02:54.299 --> 02:55.508
- [Sick Man] I am sorry.

02:56.801 --> 02:58.386
- What do you want to say to me?

03:01.556 --> 03:04.100
- [Man] I can't do it, it's a burden.

03:04.100 --> 03:07.145
- Do you want me to clear the
room so you can speak freely?

03:07.145 --> 03:09.981
(man grunting)

03:09.981 --> 03:13.318
(man faintly murmuring)

03:17.113 --> 03:20.116
(suspenseful music)

03:21.993 --> 03:24.913
(man faintly murmuring)

03:24.913 --> 03:27.582
(suspenseful music)

03:27.582 --> 03:29.876
- I said no video.

03:29.876 --> 03:31.127
That was you.

03:31.127 --> 03:32.462
- You said 57.

03:33.755 --> 03:35.715
What is 57, is that an address?

03:35.715 --> 03:39.719
(man murmuring)
(suspenseful music)

03:39.719 --> 03:41.471
- [Sick Man] I thought I blocked it out.

03:45.516 --> 03:46.434
I remember,

03:48.019 --> 03:50.146
everything that happened.

03:51.439 --> 03:53.483
- Do you mean 1957?

03:53.483 --> 03:56.486
- [Man] Yes, that's it, 57.

03:56.486 --> 03:59.447
(suspenseful music)

03:59.447 --> 04:01.532
- Go head, and confess, my son.

04:01.532 --> 04:02.367
Speak freely.

04:03.451 --> 04:04.911
God is here listening to you.

04:06.955 --> 04:08.164
(suspenseful music)

04:08.164 --> 04:10.750
(man grunting)

04:12.001 --> 04:14.462
He is here to guide you.

04:14.462 --> 04:17.048
He will guide you through your pain.

04:17.048 --> 04:18.758
Confess to God.

04:18.758 --> 04:20.635
He will relieve you of your burden.

04:20.635 --> 04:23.221
- [Sick Man] Seven, 57.

04:23.221 --> 04:26.557
(curious ambient music)

04:59.215 --> 05:00.591
- [Beatrice] Dearest Thomas,

05:01.968 --> 05:04.095
I hope you understand why I've chosen

05:04.095 --> 05:06.014
to end my disintegrating life.

05:07.807 --> 05:10.435
I could not watch myself
get any more hideous

05:10.435 --> 05:12.312
and I did not want you to see it, too.

05:14.981 --> 05:16.232
I hope when you're thinking of me,

05:16.232 --> 05:19.319
you see the beautiful
woman that you married.

05:19.319 --> 05:21.362
You have been so wonderful.

05:21.362 --> 05:24.115
And I am grateful for the
life that I had with you.

05:24.115 --> 05:26.826
(curious ambient music)

05:26.826 --> 05:29.662
I hope you were happy for
me because as you read this,

05:29.662 --> 05:31.247
I'm no longer suffering.

05:33.666 --> 05:35.043
I love you.

05:35.043 --> 05:37.420
And one day, I will see you again.

05:37.420 --> 05:40.757
(curious ambient music)

06:45.696 --> 06:47.490
(book slams)

06:47.490 --> 06:50.827
(curious ambient music)

07:06.259 --> 07:09.262
(tape, plastic crumpling)

07:09.262 --> 07:13.349
(curious ambient music)

07:13.349 --> 07:14.976
(vomit spewing)

07:14.976 --> 07:16.727
(curious ambient music)

07:16.727 --> 07:19.397
(woman gagging)

07:21.691 --> 07:25.069
(curious ambient music)

07:29.282 --> 07:31.951
(intense music)

09:16.055 --> 09:18.808
(dramatic music)

09:36.492 --> 09:37.660
(chain clinks)

09:37.660 --> 09:40.413
(woman coughing)

09:42.206 --> 09:43.249
(woman spitting)

09:43.249 --> 09:46.002
(woman coughing)

09:54.927 --> 09:57.847
(lighter flickers)

10:02.935 --> 10:05.563
- Harold, where have you been?

10:06.439 --> 10:07.898
You disappeared on me.

10:07.898 --> 10:12.278
I thought you died. (laughing)

10:12.278 --> 10:14.989
(woman coughing)

10:17.992 --> 10:20.036
(sighs) I think I need to call Dr. Valmer,

10:20.036 --> 10:20.953
who's in tomorrow.

10:21.829 --> 10:23.664
Whatever bug you've been building up,

10:23.664 --> 10:25.249
I think I caught.

10:29.545 --> 10:33.924
(coughing) Harold, have you
even heard a single word I said?

10:34.759 --> 10:37.762
(scoffs) It's no wonder
you can keep a goddamn job.

10:37.762 --> 10:40.640
You're lucky you can pay the
$90 for this month's rent.

10:40.640 --> 10:42.183
Probably gonna have to ask father again,

10:42.183 --> 10:43.476
to help bail us out.

10:48.314 --> 10:50.358
(pensive music)
You okay?

10:50.358 --> 10:52.360
You've been weird ever since Bogart died.

10:53.361 --> 10:55.446
I think I'm going to make tea.
(zombie growling)

10:55.446 --> 10:59.575
(coughing) Maybe I'll heat
up some corn beef hash, too.

10:59.575 --> 11:04.580
(woman screaming)
(intense music)

11:09.669 --> 11:11.879
(zombie growling)

11:11.879 --> 11:16.884
(woman screaming)
(intense piano music)

11:20.763 --> 11:23.182
(faint murmuring)

11:23.182 --> 11:24.183
I understand.

11:24.183 --> 11:26.060
(faint murmuring)

11:26.060 --> 11:26.977
Uh ha, bye.

11:55.715 --> 11:58.634
(typewriter key clicking)

11:58.634 --> 12:00.553
(phone rings)

12:00.553 --> 12:03.222
(Bethany sighs)

12:05.766 --> 12:10.521
(phone rings)
(typewriter keys clicking)

12:10.521 --> 12:11.939
Where have you been, mister?

12:11.939 --> 12:14.358
That darn phone has been ringing non-stop.

12:15.693 --> 12:17.153
- I'm only two minutes late.

12:17.153 --> 12:19.947
(Bethany scoffs)

12:21.282 --> 12:22.116
- Hello?

12:24.660 --> 12:28.247
(typewriter keys clicking)

12:28.247 --> 12:29.039
So...

12:30.082 --> 12:31.250
Why do you think

12:31.250 --> 12:33.878
that I wouldn't be able
to write our wedding vows?

12:33.878 --> 12:35.671
- Where is this coming from?

12:35.671 --> 12:36.672
- Well, I'm in the car,

12:36.672 --> 12:38.841
listening to the Jimmy Star
Show, on the way over here.

12:38.841 --> 12:41.135
So they start discussing wedding vows.

12:42.303 --> 12:44.680
So I clearly thought back

12:44.680 --> 12:46.474
to the other night's
dinner conversation where-

12:46.474 --> 12:49.143
(laughing) The dinner
that you were late for?

12:49.143 --> 12:51.020
Mister, I'm always on time.

12:51.020 --> 12:53.105
I'm always punctual.

12:53.105 --> 12:55.566
Mister, I'm always late
when that phone is ringing.

12:55.566 --> 12:57.735
(typewriter keys clicking)

12:57.735 --> 12:59.320
- You know what else I'm gonna be late to?

13:00.529 --> 13:01.489
Our wedding.

13:01.489 --> 13:04.325
(Bethany scoffs)

13:04.325 --> 13:06.160
- Not likely.

13:06.160 --> 13:07.453
Unless you want to be carried to the alter

13:07.453 --> 13:08.913
by two big gorillas.

13:08.913 --> 13:09.997
And Bobby will make sure that James

13:09.997 --> 13:12.541
and Charles are right there
by your side on that day.

13:12.541 --> 13:15.085
- So the gorillas are your two brothers?

13:15.085 --> 13:18.297
I'm sorry, I thought you
were referring to your folks.

13:18.297 --> 13:20.341
- Why, George Alfred Lazarus,

13:20.341 --> 13:22.301
you take that back!

13:22.301 --> 13:23.427
You take it back!

13:24.303 --> 13:26.347
(Bethany scoffs)

13:26.347 --> 13:29.642
(typewriter keys clicking)

13:29.642 --> 13:31.227
(phone rings)

13:31.227 --> 13:32.561
Pick up that-
- Insurance.

13:33.729 --> 13:35.231
Yeah, this is he.

13:36.857 --> 13:38.651
- [Bethany] Mother and
father are not going to-

13:38.651 --> 13:40.069
(George scoffs)

13:40.069 --> 13:41.445
- You don't say?

13:42.321 --> 13:44.657
No, I don't see anything here.

13:44.657 --> 13:46.325
- Your sister's a baboon.

13:46.325 --> 13:49.036
- Hmm hmm.
(Bethany playful grunting)

13:49.036 --> 13:51.455
Hold, Bethany, you got
a telegram this morning?

13:51.455 --> 13:52.248
- [Bethany] No.

13:52.248 --> 13:54.166
- Wait, Mr. George, wait.

13:54.166 --> 13:55.209
- [George] Hold on a second, here.

13:55.209 --> 13:56.669
- Good morning, Benjamin! (laughing)

13:56.669 --> 13:59.964
- [George] I'll call you back
(murmurs), give me a second.

13:59.964 --> 14:01.632
Yeah, got it, uh ha.

14:03.217 --> 14:04.051
- [Chip] Good morning, Ms. Bethany.

14:04.051 --> 14:07.847
- And how are you today?
- Eh. (laughing)

14:11.642 --> 14:13.227
- Ah, look at this.

14:14.770 --> 14:15.563
Okay.

14:17.189 --> 14:19.608
Oh, I hope that's not your
mother's blueberry pie

14:19.608 --> 14:23.070
that you got tucked in under
your arm there. (laughing)

14:23.070 --> 14:26.782
- Oh no, I picked this
up at the five and dime.

14:26.782 --> 14:28.367
It's a Frisbee.

14:28.367 --> 14:29.827
You play catch with it.

14:29.827 --> 14:30.953
Kind of like baseball,

14:30.953 --> 14:34.248
but it's with the saucer, instead.

14:34.248 --> 14:36.208
- Well, why don't you
just find a baseball?

14:36.208 --> 14:38.794
- I kind of wanted to
see how I like this first

14:38.794 --> 14:41.171
so I can send it to my
little cousin for Christmas.

14:41.171 --> 14:42.256
- Oh dear.

14:42.256 --> 14:43.799
Do you really think he's
going to enjoy playing

14:43.799 --> 14:45.092
with a pie pan?

14:46.969 --> 14:49.555
- Well, I don't know,
I hope so. (laughing)

14:49.555 --> 14:51.640
I spent all my money on a plane ticket

14:51.640 --> 14:52.683
to see the little brat,

14:52.683 --> 14:54.518
and my namesake, my Uncle Ben.

14:55.394 --> 14:57.021
I know, no rice jokes.

14:57.021 --> 14:59.398
(Bethany laughing)

14:59.398 --> 15:03.611
(George faintly talking)

15:03.611 --> 15:05.154
- I'm sure he's going to love it.

15:05.154 --> 15:05.988
- Okay, thanks.

15:06.864 --> 15:08.157
Hey, good morning, Chip.

15:10.117 --> 15:11.994
All right, so that was Hitchcock

15:11.994 --> 15:14.413
over at Topaz Insurance.

15:14.413 --> 15:15.831
A company over in Studio City

15:15.831 --> 15:18.542
just filed a claim against
some of their employees,

15:18.542 --> 15:21.837
stating that they had
sabotaged his business

15:21.837 --> 15:23.547
with some unknown source.

15:23.547 --> 15:26.258
So the owner, he wants his claim adjusted

15:26.258 --> 15:27.468
and he wants the policy pay out

15:27.468 --> 15:29.219
so it can make up for the downtime.

15:30.304 --> 15:32.848
- Well, that claim sounds like
it's both birds, Mr. George.

15:32.848 --> 15:36.268
- Hmm, yeah, well, Topaz agrees.

15:36.268 --> 15:40.856
So, they want us to dig,
see what we find out.

15:40.856 --> 15:42.691
- Well, how much is the claim for?

15:42.691 --> 15:46.320
- Well, looking at 13 people on the claim

15:46.320 --> 15:47.947
from the company,

15:47.947 --> 15:49.782
lost wages,

15:49.782 --> 15:51.367
estimated,

15:51.367 --> 15:52.618
$13 million.

15:52.618 --> 15:54.036
(Chip spits milk)

15:54.036 --> 15:55.663
(Bethany gasps)

15:55.663 --> 15:56.580
- I declare.

15:56.580 --> 15:58.457
- Well, what company
has that type of money

15:58.457 --> 16:00.459
to pay out, anyway?

16:00.459 --> 16:02.503
I don't know, it seems a little out there,

16:02.503 --> 16:04.630
like that woman who stole $40,000

16:04.630 --> 16:06.382
to pay for her boyfriend's divorce.

16:07.591 --> 16:09.927
And then she gets caught
and wants to return it.

16:09.927 --> 16:11.261
(Chip and Bethany laughing)

16:11.261 --> 16:12.638
I tell ya, people.

16:12.638 --> 16:15.474
Geez, what a psycho.

16:15.474 --> 16:17.601
- Why don't you tell us
how you really feel, Chip?

16:22.648 --> 16:26.485
- Goodbye, Ms. Bethany.
- Goodbye. (laughing)

16:26.485 --> 16:28.362
- Bye, George.

16:28.362 --> 16:31.949
(typewriter keys clicking)

16:34.076 --> 16:35.995
- Don't forget, we have
dinner tonight at the Parks.

16:35.995 --> 16:36.829
And then afterwards,

16:36.829 --> 16:39.498
all watching you bet
your life on television.

16:39.498 --> 16:41.417
- (scoffs) That was tonight, wasn't it?

16:42.251 --> 16:45.254
- No George, you did
this to them last week.

16:45.254 --> 16:46.922
We are going and that is final.

16:46.922 --> 16:48.090
- Uh ha.

16:48.090 --> 16:50.342
- George, you promised.

16:50.342 --> 16:51.218
- Hmm hmm, yeah.

16:51.218 --> 16:53.429
- George stop, you promised!

16:53.429 --> 16:54.930
- Oh, all right, all right!

16:56.432 --> 16:57.266
Until then though,

16:57.266 --> 16:58.100
I'm going down to the Valley.

16:58.100 --> 16:58.934
I've got to take a ride out there.

16:58.934 --> 17:00.644
I've got to sit down with Harry.

17:00.644 --> 17:02.271
I gotta get more details.

17:03.272 --> 17:04.356
- Well, you need company?

17:04.356 --> 17:05.357
I'm almost done here.

17:05.357 --> 17:06.775
- Nah, that's okay, love.

17:06.775 --> 17:08.235
I'll be back within the hour.

17:09.862 --> 17:10.821
- Okay, Mister.

17:11.864 --> 17:13.115
You don't want me around?

17:14.533 --> 17:15.534
I get it.

17:15.534 --> 17:19.580
(typewriter keys clicking)
- Hey.

17:21.123 --> 17:22.458
You know, you...

17:23.834 --> 17:25.961
You're my special flower.

17:26.837 --> 17:29.548
I wouldn't know what to do
if you weren't in my life.

17:30.966 --> 17:31.967
You keep me honest.

17:34.386 --> 17:35.554
You keep me grounded.

17:37.806 --> 17:38.974
And you keep me humble.

17:40.726 --> 17:41.977
And these are some of the things

17:41.977 --> 17:43.437
that I truly love about you.

17:45.481 --> 17:46.982
(lips smacks)

17:46.982 --> 17:47.775
You see?

17:49.276 --> 17:50.986
I could write my vows.

17:50.986 --> 17:53.447
- (laughing) Take me with you.

17:53.447 --> 17:54.490
- I certainly will.

17:55.491 --> 17:56.742
And this...

18:01.747 --> 18:04.291
This is what you got me
for my birthday last year.

18:06.794 --> 18:09.755
Man, I'm killing this vow stuff!

18:09.755 --> 18:13.008
- Oh, what am I gonna do with you?

18:13.008 --> 18:14.093
(muffled DJ on radio)

18:14.093 --> 18:15.469
- [DJ On Radio] Stated
that Jackie Robinson

18:15.469 --> 18:17.137
will not be moving with
the Brooklyn Dodgers

18:17.137 --> 18:18.722
when they relocate to Los Angeles...

18:18.722 --> 18:23.727
(upbeat music)
(faint chattering)

18:26.021 --> 18:27.606
- [George] Hey Smitty, what do you say?

18:27.606 --> 18:28.732
- Hey, George, the usual?

18:28.732 --> 18:29.817
- Yes, with a Tribune.

18:30.734 --> 18:32.444
You like the fights, George.

18:32.444 --> 18:33.529
- Hasn't been exciting to me

18:33.529 --> 18:35.906
since my Marciano retired last year.

18:35.906 --> 18:38.909
(upbeat music)
(overlapping chattering)

18:38.909 --> 18:42.162
- Big talker today, I see. (laughs)

18:42.162 --> 18:43.539
Okay, one A cream.

18:45.332 --> 18:47.543
Ed Gein, is that that killer's name?

18:50.045 --> 18:51.130
I've heard about him.

18:52.214 --> 18:53.882
Good, they caught him.

18:53.882 --> 18:56.051
Have you been following
that story, George?

18:57.845 --> 18:59.888
Pretty interesting stuff.

18:59.888 --> 19:01.431
Hey, it could make a good book, one day.

19:01.431 --> 19:05.394
(upbeat music)
(overlapping chattering)

19:05.394 --> 19:06.520
Oh, what's the use?

19:06.520 --> 19:08.272
That'll be the usual, 25 cents.

19:09.565 --> 19:11.775
- I was hoping you'd throw me
a curve on your price, Smitty.

19:11.775 --> 19:12.943
- Curve balls?

19:12.943 --> 19:14.403
Hey, in April, you can
see as many as you like

19:14.403 --> 19:15.988
when the Dodgers play.

19:15.988 --> 19:19.408
- Says here, Robinson is
thinking of retiring this year.

19:19.408 --> 19:21.285
- You don't say, really?

19:21.285 --> 19:22.703
What a bum.

19:22.703 --> 19:24.371
Let New York keep 'em.

19:24.371 --> 19:27.666
I hear they're still pretty
upset that they're moving here.

19:27.666 --> 19:29.835
Maybe we'll take their
beloved Yankees, too,

19:29.835 --> 19:31.670
and have all three of
their teams, right George?

19:31.670 --> 19:33.380
- It would never happen.

19:33.380 --> 19:36.216
- Jumping Joe is always
out here anyways, George.

19:36.216 --> 19:37.676
You know what I mean?

19:37.676 --> 19:42.181
Jumping Joe, he's always
out here anyways. (laughing)

19:42.181 --> 19:43.223
Get it?

19:43.223 --> 19:45.559
Jumping Joe, he's always out here.

19:45.559 --> 19:46.393
He's always here, anyways.

19:46.393 --> 19:48.103
- See you tomorrow, Smitty.

19:48.103 --> 19:49.688
- [Smitty] He's always here.

19:49.688 --> 19:51.398
- I don't get it, Smitty.

19:51.398 --> 19:53.567
- Just drink your shake, Bub.

19:53.567 --> 19:58.322
(upbeat music)
(overlapping chattering)

19:58.322 --> 20:01.116
(birds chirping)

20:09.416 --> 20:10.876
(fire crackling)

20:10.876 --> 20:15.881
(bells tolling)
(suspenseful music)

20:16.215 --> 20:18.842
(Steven moans)

20:19.718 --> 20:22.721
(suspenseful music)

20:32.981 --> 20:35.859
(phone trills)

20:35.859 --> 20:38.987
- Operator?
- Yes, operator.

20:38.987 --> 20:41.198
Please, fetch me the police.

20:41.198 --> 20:43.158
- [Operator] Is this an emergency, sir?

20:43.158 --> 20:47.162
- Yes, thank you.
- Please hold.

20:47.162 --> 20:48.497
- [Police] Los Angeles Police Department.

20:48.497 --> 20:49.498
Sergeant Jone's speaking.

20:49.498 --> 20:51.166
Who am I speaking with, please?

20:51.166 --> 20:52.167
(suspenseful music)

20:52.167 --> 20:54.628
- This is Steven Wells.

20:54.628 --> 20:56.380
- [Police] What's your
emergency, Mr. Wells?

20:56.380 --> 20:59.758
- Sir, I would like to record a murder.

20:59.758 --> 21:01.593
- [Police] A murder, did
you say a murder, Mr. Wells?

21:01.593 --> 21:04.596
(suspenseful music)

21:04.596 --> 21:09.184
- I think I killed my
wife. (labored breathing)

21:09.184 --> 21:10.352
Again.

21:10.352 --> 21:12.104
- [Police] Sir, what
exactly, what are you saying?

21:12.104 --> 21:15.482
(suspenseful music)

