43:32.401 --> 43:34.945
since when do I go to the
production room, MacMan?

43:34.945 --> 43:36.238
- You've just gotta come
to production room one.

43:36.238 --> 43:37.406
- What is it, Jimmy?

43:37.406 --> 43:38.240
Is it Jimmy, again?

43:38.240 --> 43:39.116
I told you it's Jimmy.

43:39.116 --> 43:41.285
He should've got rid of Jimmy
a long time ago, little girl.

43:41.285 --> 43:43.287
Go see what he wants!

43:43.287 --> 43:44.330
- Yes father, I'll handle it.

43:44.330 --> 43:45.664
- Yeah, you'll handle it.

43:45.664 --> 43:46.540
You'll handle everything.

43:46.540 --> 43:47.458
You want to handle people.

43:47.458 --> 43:49.043
You want to keep people on the payroll.

43:49.043 --> 43:51.712
If we don't need them, we don't need 'em!

43:51.712 --> 43:55.007
(Mammon breathing heavily)

43:55.007 --> 43:57.259
(woman screaming)

43:57.259 --> 44:00.763
Take that screaming woman out of here.

44:00.763 --> 44:05.559
(woman screaming)
- Calm down, calm down.

44:06.727 --> 44:09.271
- Little girl, you don't need to see this.

44:10.564 --> 44:12.149
- [Lucinda] Okay.

44:12.149 --> 44:16.695
- Lucinda, darling, you
don't need to see this.

44:18.030 --> 44:20.282
You don't need to look at this.

44:20.282 --> 44:23.619
(suspenseful music)
(moaning)

44:23.619 --> 44:24.453
MacMan!

44:25.996 --> 44:28.999
(suspenseful music)

44:31.502 --> 44:32.461
Clean this up.

44:34.505 --> 44:36.590
Clean it all up.

44:36.590 --> 44:38.801
MacMan, what do you think
you're doing with that?

44:38.801 --> 44:40.386
- We can throw it out with them.

44:40.386 --> 44:42.429
- (laughing) Throw it out with them, see?

44:44.598 --> 44:46.642
- Tossing it out, tossing it out.

44:46.642 --> 44:48.185
You see what I'm doing here, MacMan?

44:48.185 --> 44:49.228
You see what I'm doing?

44:49.228 --> 44:50.479
I'm tossing my money away.

44:50.479 --> 44:52.231
Why don't you do the same
thing with my investment.

44:52.231 --> 44:53.816
Now, clean that up,

44:53.816 --> 44:57.695
wipe it down and get
all this nice and clean.

44:58.529 --> 45:01.031
- But-
- No butts, MacMan.

45:01.031 --> 45:03.117
- But, it's contaminated.

45:04.326 --> 45:07.913
- (laughing) Contaminated?

45:07.913 --> 45:10.916
(suspenseful music)

45:12.376 --> 45:15.212
This is what you're going to do, MacMan.

45:15.212 --> 45:17.131
You're going to clean up my investment.

45:17.131 --> 45:20.008
You're going to put it
in that machine, you see?

45:20.008 --> 45:22.219
And you're gonna run
production as planned.

45:26.432 --> 45:28.934
And you're gonna take my product

45:28.934 --> 45:31.437
and you're going to put it in a pallet.

45:31.437 --> 45:34.231
You're going to store the
pallet in a warehouse, MacMan.

45:36.233 --> 45:38.944
And you're going to take 13 employees,

45:38.944 --> 45:40.362
whoever you want.

45:40.362 --> 45:41.822
I don't care.

45:41.822 --> 45:45.743
You're going to reward them
as employees of the month.

45:45.743 --> 45:47.494
You'll take their pictures.

45:47.494 --> 45:49.163
You'll hang them up in the lobby.

45:50.372 --> 45:53.792
(scoffs) And then, Mr. MacMan (laughs),

45:54.877 --> 45:57.045
you're going to take my investment.

45:57.045 --> 45:59.298
You're going to ship it out.

45:59.298 --> 46:00.966
And we're gonna wait.

46:02.468 --> 46:05.888
(suspenseful music)

46:05.888 --> 46:07.973
Do I make myself clear, Mr. MacMan?

46:07.973 --> 46:08.807
Because...

46:10.476 --> 46:11.810
I won't hesitate.

46:11.810 --> 46:15.105
I will shoot you right here, right now,

46:15.105 --> 46:16.732
right where you stand.

46:17.608 --> 46:21.695
Do I make myself clear, Mr. MacMan?

46:24.156 --> 46:29.161
(sinister laughing)
(suspenseful music)

46:44.718 --> 46:48.180
(overlapping city sounds)

47:02.444 --> 47:05.739
(rhythmic music)

47:05.739 --> 47:10.744
(overlapping chattering)
(pop surf music)

47:10.744 --> 47:12.120
- Look at this menu.

47:13.455 --> 47:17.042
This is George's favorite thing
to eat, burgers and shakes.

47:17.042 --> 47:19.503
He loved it more than
anything else in this world.

47:20.754 --> 47:23.757
Well, not the hot plate of corn beef hash.

47:23.757 --> 47:26.802
George loved that, too. (laughing)

47:26.802 --> 47:29.596
On the other hand, he
really didn't like liver.

47:29.596 --> 47:32.850
I mean, I couldn't get that
man to eat liver. (laughing)

47:32.850 --> 47:35.102
- Well my Uncle Ben always
takes us to this burger place

47:35.102 --> 47:36.061
in Pennsylvania.

47:36.895 --> 47:38.480
It's up near Milford.

47:38.480 --> 47:40.524
Madison's Madness.

47:40.524 --> 47:43.068
They're famous for being
crazy with their food.

47:43.068 --> 47:45.904
- (laughing) I have no
idea what that means.

47:45.904 --> 47:47.781
- They form characters out of their food.

47:47.781 --> 47:49.908
Well, let's say for instance,

47:49.908 --> 47:52.494
you order a short stack of pancakes.

47:52.494 --> 47:54.079
They call it the village.

47:54.079 --> 47:56.498
And they design it to look like a scene

47:56.498 --> 47:57.791
from the three little pigs. (laughing)

47:57.791 --> 47:59.418
- [Bethany] No!

47:59.418 --> 48:01.795
- Well, the pancakes will be the house

48:01.795 --> 48:04.006
with the little sausages
living inside of it.

48:04.006 --> 48:05.591
It's the three little pigs.

48:05.591 --> 48:07.134
That's what I mean, weird stuff like that.

48:07.134 --> 48:08.802
- That sounds like a cute place.

48:08.802 --> 48:09.636
- It is.

48:10.929 --> 48:12.389
It's fun.

48:12.389 --> 48:14.016
It's a bit odd but fun.

48:14.016 --> 48:15.809
Traditionally, we go
there after he takes us

48:15.809 --> 48:18.103
to see the civil war reenactments.

48:18.103 --> 48:18.896
It's cool,

48:18.896 --> 48:21.690
they dress up and they
reenact the battles.

48:21.690 --> 48:24.109
- Wow, it sounds exciting.
- It's cool, it's cool.

48:24.109 --> 48:25.819
- George is such a history buff,

48:25.819 --> 48:28.614
he would have loved that. (laughs)

48:28.614 --> 48:31.241
- But do you know what
I really find weird is?

48:31.241 --> 48:34.119
Okay, I have another cousin,

48:34.119 --> 48:36.038
lives in Wilmington, North Carolina.

48:37.164 --> 48:41.418
They, too, have a civil
war reenactment. (laughing)

48:41.418 --> 48:43.754
- Okay, so what's wrong with that?

48:43.754 --> 48:46.673
- Well, well, you're in the South.

48:46.673 --> 48:48.133
I mean, you lost the war.

48:48.967 --> 48:50.844
Why would you want to
continue to reenact something

48:50.844 --> 48:52.137
that you lost?

48:52.137 --> 48:54.264
It's not like the outcome
is going to be different.

48:54.264 --> 48:55.557
I mean, am I right?

48:55.557 --> 48:57.309
- [Bethany] (laughing) You're right.

48:59.019 --> 49:00.562
- Excuse me, would you mind moving

49:00.562 --> 49:01.980
to the other side of the room?

49:01.980 --> 49:04.733
(surf pop music)

49:12.491 --> 49:13.784
- Chip, don't move.

49:16.036 --> 49:17.996
(music abruptly stops)

49:17.996 --> 49:19.247
No, thank you.

49:19.247 --> 49:20.749
We're fine right here.

49:22.584 --> 49:24.336
- Look, I don't want any trouble.

49:24.336 --> 49:25.629
Just eat your food and go.

49:30.634 --> 49:32.010
- I hate bigots.

49:33.178 --> 49:33.971
- That's okay.

49:41.186 --> 49:42.020
Thank you,

49:43.355 --> 49:44.648
for what you just did.

49:46.608 --> 49:47.609
That meant a lot.

49:48.610 --> 49:53.615
(pensive instrumental music)
(overlapping chattering)

49:56.076 --> 49:57.327
- Do you think he's okay?

50:03.041 --> 50:05.210
- We're gonna find him, Ms. Bethany.

50:05.210 --> 50:06.003
- I'm mean this,

50:07.504 --> 50:09.840
this is just so not like George.

50:09.840 --> 50:12.259
He was just by the book,
by the book of rules,

50:12.259 --> 50:13.552
thoughtful, punctual.

50:13.552 --> 50:14.636
Even if he was going to
be a few minutes late,

50:14.636 --> 50:15.929
he always called.

50:15.929 --> 50:17.347
- Well, well, we, we...

50:18.265 --> 50:20.350
we searched all the hospitals in the area.

50:21.643 --> 50:25.022
We visited all the surrounding
area police stations.

50:25.022 --> 50:27.149
I mean, they're even helping us with this,

50:27.149 --> 50:29.735
so I don't even know
what else we could do.

50:29.735 --> 50:33.530
(pensive instrumental music)

50:34.781 --> 50:37.284
- I just feel like the
only thing we can do is,

50:37.284 --> 50:38.368
what we've been doing.

50:39.953 --> 50:41.538
Back track his steps.

50:41.538 --> 50:45.250
(pensive instrumental music)

50:46.126 --> 50:48.336
- Well, what's next on that list of yours?

50:48.336 --> 50:51.131
(pensive instrumental music)

50:51.131 --> 50:53.550
- Hi, are you ready to order?

50:53.550 --> 50:57.012
(overlapping chattering)

51:04.019 --> 51:06.772
(birds chirping)

51:09.733 --> 51:10.984
- Hello?

51:10.984 --> 51:13.695
(birds chirping)

51:15.906 --> 51:17.491
(door creaking)

51:17.491 --> 51:18.992
Hello?

51:18.992 --> 51:21.787
(birds chirping)

51:21.787 --> 51:22.996
Howard?

51:22.996 --> 51:25.832
(birds chirping)

51:25.832 --> 51:28.835
(suspenseful music)

51:35.717 --> 51:37.594
(light knocking) Hello?

51:37.594 --> 51:42.599
(birds chirping)
(suspenseful music)

51:44.017 --> 51:45.018
Howard?

51:45.018 --> 51:46.520
Howard Caine?

51:46.520 --> 51:49.523
(suspenseful music)

51:54.736 --> 51:56.655
Howard, hello?

51:56.655 --> 51:58.198
I'm George Lazarus.

51:58.198 --> 52:01.326
(suspenseful music)

52:12.504 --> 52:14.256
(light knocking) Howard?

52:15.423 --> 52:16.550
Mr. Caine?

52:16.550 --> 52:19.511
(suspenseful music)

52:20.887 --> 52:24.057
(door creaking)

52:24.057 --> 52:26.226
Hello? (light knocking)

52:26.226 --> 52:29.354
(suspenseful music)

52:29.354 --> 52:30.355
Hello, Mr. Caine.

52:30.355 --> 52:33.400
(suspenseful music)

52:37.445 --> 52:38.655
(light knocking) Hello?

52:39.865 --> 52:40.782
(suspenseful music)

52:40.782 --> 52:41.658
Howard?

52:43.076 --> 52:44.119
Hello?

52:44.119 --> 52:47.122
(suspenseful music)

52:50.417 --> 52:51.418
Howard?

52:51.418 --> 52:53.378
(suspenseful music)

52:53.378 --> 52:54.171
Anybody home? (gasps)

52:54.171 --> 52:57.549
- [Eve] Poking around people's
property will get your shot.

52:57.549 --> 53:00.385
- Listen, I'm looking for Howard Caine.

53:00.385 --> 53:01.511
I'm George A. Lazarus.

53:01.511 --> 53:03.805
I work with Topaz Insurance.
- Insurance?

53:03.805 --> 53:04.598
- Is this his home?

53:04.598 --> 53:06.683
'Cause I was told that
I could find him here.

53:06.683 --> 53:07.809
I was told by Eddie,

53:07.809 --> 53:10.687
Eddie, Eddie, Eddie and Wanda Martinez?

53:10.687 --> 53:13.565
- What, I don't know them from Adam.

53:13.565 --> 53:15.275
(suspenseful music)

53:15.275 --> 53:16.568
Insurance, huh?

53:16.568 --> 53:19.154
(suspenseful music)

53:19.154 --> 53:21.156
Turn around.
(ominous music)

53:21.156 --> 53:22.824
Real slow.
- Sure, sure.

53:25.035 --> 53:26.161
- You can put your hands down.

53:26.161 --> 53:26.995
- Okay.

53:29.581 --> 53:30.999
- Insurance, huh?
- Yeah.

53:38.423 --> 53:39.883
- Yeah, Howard does live here.

53:41.593 --> 53:42.594
I'm his wife.

53:45.055 --> 53:46.264
May I get you something?

53:50.310 --> 53:53.188
Pop?

53:53.188 --> 53:55.315
Coffee, tea?

53:55.315 --> 53:56.358
- Pop sounds great.

53:57.776 --> 53:59.653
Much appreciated, madame.

53:59.653 --> 54:01.947
- (laughing) Oh, I am
not no madame, nmm, hmm.

54:08.453 --> 54:09.371
Name's Eve.

54:10.872 --> 54:12.290
Want one?

54:12.290 --> 54:13.166
- No thank you, no thank you.

54:13.166 --> 54:14.542
I don't smoke.

54:14.542 --> 54:16.503
Appreciate it.
- Really?

54:16.503 --> 54:17.337
Hmm.

54:19.172 --> 54:23.051
He's probably around back working
on that car in the garage.

54:24.052 --> 54:26.471
He loves tinkering on that thing.

54:27.472 --> 54:28.682
He's making it his life mission

54:28.682 --> 54:31.226
to get that car running again.

54:31.226 --> 54:33.895
(curious music)

54:36.523 --> 54:38.775
What'd you want to talk
to my husband about?

54:40.568 --> 54:42.487
Insurance?
- Yeah.

54:42.487 --> 54:44.489
- 'Cause we're not interested.

54:46.032 --> 54:47.242
Hell, it's hard enough to come up

54:47.242 --> 54:48.201
with the mortgage each month,

54:48.201 --> 54:49.661
for this here dump,

54:50.787 --> 54:53.790
ever since Howard lost
his job at the plant.

54:53.790 --> 54:56.835
(suspenseful music)

54:58.378 --> 54:59.838
Darned thing, too.

55:01.506 --> 55:03.925
Reward him as employee of the month.

55:03.925 --> 55:05.427
Gave him a case of smokes.

55:05.427 --> 55:07.929
Even put his picture in the paper.

55:07.929 --> 55:10.557
Smack dab on page seven of the Tribune,

55:10.557 --> 55:12.684
right next to Bogart dying.

55:12.684 --> 55:15.353
(suspenseful music)

55:15.353 --> 55:16.688
So strange.

55:19.065 --> 55:20.442
- Is that right?
- Hmm hmm.

55:21.318 --> 55:22.527
- I told Howard, see,

55:22.527 --> 55:24.237
you ain't even gotta be a movie star

55:24.237 --> 55:27.532
to get in the paper. (laughs)

55:27.532 --> 55:30.410
Just have to do business with the devil.

55:32.245 --> 55:33.246
- The devil?

55:34.622 --> 55:35.999
I don't understand.

55:41.254 --> 55:43.340
- My husband isn't right.

55:44.716 --> 55:45.550
He's sick.

55:47.677 --> 55:49.554
He got some kind of bug at the plant.

55:56.144 --> 55:57.896
I took him to the doctors

55:57.896 --> 55:59.731
and they stated that,

55:59.731 --> 56:02.609
maybe he got stung by some killer bee

56:02.609 --> 56:04.569
or maybe he's allergic or something.

56:09.157 --> 56:09.991
See...

56:11.284 --> 56:12.786
We have a beehive in the back

56:12.786 --> 56:14.454
and Howard tends to them all the time.

56:14.454 --> 56:16.122
So he is not allergic!

56:19.000 --> 56:21.211
No.
(suspenseful music)

56:21.211 --> 56:26.216
No, no sir.

56:26.508 --> 56:29.344
Something at that plant
did something to my Howard.

56:30.595 --> 56:33.640
- Eve, I need to speak to Howard.

56:33.640 --> 56:34.474
I've got to sit down.

56:34.474 --> 56:35.308
I got to talk to him.

56:35.308 --> 56:36.768
I got to ask him some routine questions,

56:36.768 --> 56:38.061
I need to get answered.

56:38.061 --> 56:39.354
- He's in the back.

56:39.354 --> 56:42.357
(suspenseful music)

56:45.443 --> 56:46.444
- Thank you.

56:47.612 --> 56:48.696
Good day.

56:48.696 --> 56:51.658
(suspenseful music)

57:27.652 --> 57:31.656
(birds chirping)
(slight groaning)

57:31.656 --> 57:33.366
- Howard, Mr. Caine?

57:34.451 --> 57:37.203
(metal clanking)

57:39.456 --> 57:42.709
- I heard you talking
to my wife, Mr. Lazarus.

57:46.212 --> 57:49.090
Normally, I would introduce myself

57:49.090 --> 57:51.176
and shake your hand.

57:54.679 --> 57:56.681
But the way you're staring at me suggests

57:56.681 --> 58:01.686
I must look worse than I
did yesterday. (gasping)

58:04.189 --> 58:06.107
- Yeah, I'm sorry, Mr. Caine.

58:06.107 --> 58:07.317
I didn't mean to.

58:07.317 --> 58:08.860
- Tell you the truth (gasping),

58:09.777 --> 58:11.404
I haven't looked at myself today.

58:12.906 --> 58:15.825
I didn't like what I
saw yesterday. (laughs)

58:20.788 --> 58:23.458
- Mr. Caine.
- Doctors tell me...

58:23.458 --> 58:26.127
Nothing's wrong. (gasping)

58:31.007 --> 58:32.467
- Sir?

58:32.467 --> 58:34.511
I'm here, I'm investigating a claim

58:34.511 --> 58:36.471
that was placed by your former employer,

58:36.471 --> 58:37.805
Deadly Sin Cigarettes.

58:38.723 --> 58:41.643
- I don't feel like
talking much these days,

58:41.643 --> 58:44.187
especially about those bastards.

58:45.230 --> 58:47.440
So, I won't waste your time.

58:49.567 --> 58:50.860
Head down to the lounge.

58:52.904 --> 58:55.281
On Vermont. (gasping)

58:55.281 --> 58:56.449
See Roger Abel.

58:58.326 --> 58:59.452
- Roger Abel?

59:00.828 --> 59:02.372
Sir, I don't have a Roger Abel.

59:02.372 --> 59:04.791
I don't have a Roger Abel
on my list, Mr. Caine.

59:04.791 --> 59:07.460
(labored breathing)

59:07.460 --> 59:08.795
Mr. Caine.

59:08.795 --> 59:11.881
- You must have the
employee of the month list.

59:11.881 --> 59:13.174
Roger wouldn't be on that.

59:15.051 --> 59:16.469
But he was there.

59:17.595 --> 59:21.641
And he was let go, as well. (gasping)

59:21.641 --> 59:22.475
Well...

59:24.310 --> 59:25.186
Talk to Roger.

59:25.979 --> 59:27.355
He loves to talk.

59:28.690 --> 59:30.483
Now, I'd appreciate it,

59:30.483 --> 59:33.903
if you let me be. (gasping)

59:33.903 --> 59:35.405
Please, please go.

59:36.781 --> 59:39.617
Please (gasping).

59:41.911 --> 59:43.079
- Good day, Mr. Caine.

59:44.289 --> 59:47.875
(Howard breathing heavily)

1:00:03.725 --> 1:00:06.519
(Howard sobbing)

1:00:12.817 --> 1:00:16.362
(Howard breathing heavily)

1:00:25.121 --> 1:00:29.751
My Lord. (gasps)

1:00:29.751 --> 1:00:32.629
I'm sorry for my sins.

1:00:32.629 --> 1:00:34.130
With my all heart,

1:00:37.050 --> 1:00:40.136
in choosing to do wrong.

1:00:40.136 --> 1:00:42.013
I'm saying to you, God.

1:00:43.139 --> 1:00:45.892
(Howard sobbing)

1:00:48.311 --> 1:00:50.313
I've sinned against you.

1:00:54.484 --> 1:00:57.278
(Howard sobbing)

1:01:04.577 --> 1:01:09.582
(engine starts)
(somber music)

1:01:10.375 --> 1:01:13.378
(suspenseful music)

1:02:04.929 --> 1:02:08.057
- Hello?
(dramatic music)

1:02:08.057 --> 1:02:09.851
(ominous music)

1:02:09.851 --> 1:02:11.018
Mrs. Caine?

1:02:11.018 --> 1:02:13.688
(ominous music)

1:02:24.365 --> 1:02:25.241
Hello!

1:02:26.659 --> 1:02:29.370
(ominous music)

1:02:31.289 --> 1:02:33.833
(door rattling)

1:02:33.833 --> 1:02:35.960
- You find anything?
- No.

1:02:38.254 --> 1:02:40.882
(ominous music)

1:02:44.385 --> 1:02:47.096
(door squeaking)

1:02:48.723 --> 1:02:49.974
- Ms. Bethany!
- What?

1:02:49.974 --> 1:02:51.392
- This door is open.

1:02:51.392 --> 1:02:52.894
- Let's see if someone's inside.

1:02:54.061 --> 1:02:55.271
(dog barking)

1:02:55.271 --> 1:02:56.856
Ready?

1:02:56.856 --> 1:02:58.858
- [Chip] Yep, I'm ready.

1:03:01.027 --> 1:03:01.903
- [Bethany] Hello!

1:03:10.703 --> 1:03:13.122
- Now why did I know that
it was going to happen?

1:03:14.123 --> 1:03:17.001
Oh, I have a light that
I use for my camera.

1:03:17.001 --> 1:03:18.127
It doesn't last long,

1:03:18.127 --> 1:03:21.047
